cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a unified probabilistic model for learning the latent space of imaging data and performing supervised regression. It uses recent advances in learning disentangled representations and performs a variational inference procedure. The application is to predict the age of subjects from their structural Magnetic Resonance (MR) images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses a neural-network regressor, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with neuroimage analysis, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
